Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_58.HTM#Sec6>

Foot and mouth disease in Mongolia
----------------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of foot and mouth disease in Mongolia reported
to the OIE: August 2002).
This emergency report is from information received on 12 Feb 2004 from Dr
Ravdan Sanjaatogtokh, director of the State Veterinary Services, Ministry
of Food and Agriculture, Ulaanbaatar:
Date of the report: 11 Feb 2004.
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Estimated date of primary infection: 7 Feb 2004.
Outbreaks:
Location / No. of outbreaks
Dornogobi Province, Urgun county (in south-eastern Mongolia) / 1
Dornogobi Province, Altanshiree county / 1
Dornogobi Province, Sainshand county / 1
Description of affected population: domestic cattle and sheep. Foot and
mouth disease (FMD) has also been confirmed in nomadic wild antelopes in
the affected area.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
bov / 687 / 157 / ... / 157 / ...
ovi / 1632 / 276 / ... / 276 / ...
cap / 1782 / ... / ... / ... / ...
cml / 53 / ... / ... / ... / ...
The diagnosis of the causal agent -- FMD virus type O -- was made at the
State Central Veterinary Laboratory, Ulaanbaatar, using liquid-phase
blocking enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) (FMD virus types O, A,
Asia1 - Pirbright Laboratory, United Kingdom); antibody detection ELISA
(FMD virus type O); ELISA 3B; ELISA 3ABC for detection of antibodies to non
structural virus proteins.
Source of agent / origin of infection: suspected to be due to the migration
of wild antelope. Source of agent is under investigation.
Control measures:
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- vaccination;
- zoning.
--
